description:
&lt;p&gt;Medicine &amp; Emergency Care are inviting registered nurses to apply for positions within their Division.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking to welcome you to one of three Care Units within our Division where you will have the opportunity to work in one area or build a rotational/development package to enable you to gain a full insight.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Acute Care Unit&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Covering our Emergency Department, Emergency Management Unit, Short Stay Unit, Triage and Frailty.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Specialty Care Unit&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Inclusive of Acute Stroke, Stroke Rehab, Haematology, Oncology and Endocrinology&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;General Medicine Care Unit&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Cardiology, Respiratory, Care of the Elderly, Gastroenterology&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;All areas are supported with a senior leadership team, a clinical ward matron and a team of band 6 nurses.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;We will support your career progression via our onsite education centre, clinical skills team, clinical educators and speciality competency booklets&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Please note if you are a final year student and would like to apply please email joanne.cowlishaw@nhs.net or clairedavies4@nhs.net&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Senior Matrons Jane Parkin (Acute Care Unit), Sally Upton (General Care Unit), Gary Durrant (Specialty Care Unit) are contactable via 01246 513403&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Alternatively; contact our Recruitment Coordinator joanne.cowlishaw@nhs.net or our Nursing Workforce Coordinator clairedavies4@nhs.net who would be happy to arrange informal visits.&lt;/p&gt;
